---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '@/components/hero/PageHero.astro';
import CTABanner from '@/components/cta/CTABanner.astro';
import { url } from '@/utils/url';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About | QBITEL Bridge"
  description="Learn about QBITEL Bridge's mission, vision, open-source philosophy, and the team building the future of protocol intelligence."
>
  <PageHero
    title="About QBITEL Bridge"
    description="We are building the protocol intelligence platform that bridges the gap between legacy infrastructure and modern, quantum-safe systems."
    badge="Open Source"
  />

  <!-- Mission and Vision -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-surface-600/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Our Mission</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Billions of dollars in critical infrastructure runs on undocumented, proprietary protocols that no one fully understands. These systems power financial transactions, healthcare records, manufacturing processes, and government operations. When the engineers who built them retire, organizations face an impossible choice: maintain systems they cannot understand, or undertake risky, multi-year migration projects.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            QBITEL Bridge exists to eliminate that dilemma. We use AI to reverse-engineer any protocol, generate modern APIs and adapters, and secure everything with post-quantum cryptography -- all without modifying the original systems.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Our Vision</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We envision a world where no organization is held hostage by undocumented protocols. Where legacy systems can be understood, secured, and modernized in days instead of years. Where the transition to quantum-safe cryptography happens gradually and safely, without forklift upgrades.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            QBITEL Bridge is the platform that makes this possible: an AI-powered bridge between the systems of yesterday and the security requirements of tomorrow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Open Source -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-surface-600/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="section-heading">
          Why <span class="gradient-text">Open Source</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-subheading mx-auto">
          Security infrastructure should be transparent, auditable, and community-driven. Here is why we chose to build QBITEL Bridge in the open.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-quantum-500/10 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-quantum-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M2.458 12C3.732 7.943 7.523 5 12 5c4.478 0 8.268 2.943 9.542 7-1.274 4.057-5.064 7-9.542 7-4.477 0-8.268-2.943-9.542-7z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">Transparency</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            When security is your product, your users need to verify it. Open source means every cryptographic implementation, every AI model decision, and every security policy can be audited by anyone.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-quantum-500/10 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-quantum-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">Community</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            Protocol expertise is distributed across thousands of engineers worldwide. An open-source model lets anyone contribute protocol parsers, security rules, and compliance frameworks that benefit the entire ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-quantum-500/10 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-quantum-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">Trust</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            Organizations deploying security infrastructure in critical environments need to trust the software. Open source eliminates vendor lock-in and gives teams full control over their deployment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Technology Stack -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-surface-600/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="section-heading">
          Built With <span class="gradient-text">Modern Technology</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-subheading mx-auto">
          QBITEL Bridge is a polyglot platform, using the right language for each component to maximize performance, safety, and developer productivity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Python</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">AI Engine</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Protocol discovery, ML inference, LLM orchestration, compliance assessment</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Rust</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Data Plane</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Wire-speed packet processing, PQC encryption, DPDK-accelerated I/O</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Go</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Control Plane</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Policy engine, device management, Kubernetes operator, API gateway</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">TypeScript</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">UI Console</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">React dashboard, real-time visualizations, protocol inspector</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Project Stats -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-surface-600/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="section-heading">
          By the <span class="gradient-text">Numbers</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold gradient-text mb-1">150k+</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400">Lines of Code</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold gradient-text mb-1">10</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400">Integrated Products</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold gradient-text mb-1">4</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400">Languages</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-6 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold gradient-text mb-1">Apache 2.0</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400">License</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team Philosophy -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="section-heading">
          Built by <span class="gradient-text">Engineers, for Engineers</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          QBITEL Bridge is built by a team of security researchers, protocol engineers, and infrastructure architects who have spent years working with legacy systems in financial services, healthcare, government, and critical infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          We believe that the best security tools are the ones engineers actually want to use. That means clean APIs, comprehensive documentation, sensible defaults, and a developer experience that respects your time.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
          <a href={url('/community')} class="btn-primary">
            Join the Community
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 ml-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
            </svg>
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/yazhsab/qbitel-bridge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-secondary">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/>
            </svg>
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
